                <head>356. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On January 21, 1957, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_BEO1">Briggs</persName> and
                    Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs Macedo Soares exchanged notes at Rio de
                    Janeiro regarding an agreement for the establishment of a guided missiles
                    facility on the island of Fernando de Noronha. The agreement entered into force
                    on the same date. For text, see 8 UST 87 or Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, February 25, 1957, pages 316–317. Ambassador
                        <persName corresp="#p_BEO1">Briggs</persName> reported the signing ceremony
                    to the Department in telegram 738 from Rio de Janeiro, January 21. (Department
                    of State, Central Files, 732.5–<gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/1–2157)</p>
            </div>
